<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-134-096 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 814 530</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  June 7 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software cuts some jail costs by 50%. (JALAN's JAIL turnkey jailmanagement system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mallory, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Jalan Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   JAIL (Turnkey system) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Correctional institutionsTurnkey SystemsLaw enforcementComputer industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SOFTWARE CUTS SOME JAIL COSTS BY 50% 06/07/91 SPOKANE, WASHINGTON, U.S.A.,andO;1991 JUN 7 (NB) -- JALAN has announced it has sold its JAIL system to Pricor,a private jail company headquartered in Tennessee.andP;  JALAN says this will bethe first purchase of a computerized jail management system by Pricor.andP;  Thesystem will be installed at the Angelina County Corrections Facility inDiboll, Texas, with five other Texas facilities to be installed in thefuture.andM;According to Jan Robinson, president of JALAN, the system documents anoffender's activity from the minute he is taken into the jail.andP;  It trackscourt appearances, medical visits, personal belongings, funds, and otherdetails.andP;  Robinson says the system &quot;practically makes paperwork obsolete anddecreases booking time by 50 percent or more.&quot;andM;JALAN's prosecutors system was recently recognized by the Western RegionGovernment Technology Conference with its &quot;Featured Solution&quot; award.andP;  JALANsays it has installations of its specialized software for the criminaljustice field in 21 states and the Virgin Islands.andM;(Jim Mallory/19910607/Press Contact:Maria Ranniger, Robideaux andamp; Assoc,509-838-1036)</TEXT></DOC>